<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Counselor of Embassy in China (
                        Smyth
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d139</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">139</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-02-08T21:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-02-08T21:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-08T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-08T21:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_FEAC1">FEAC</gloss>/2–946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-09T09:00:00+07:00">February 9, 1946—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>252. Substance of <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>’s 121, Jan 18<note n="78" xml:id="d139fn1">Telegram 121, January 18, quoted from telegram 150, January
                        17, from Moscow, (<ref target="#pg_111">p. 111</ref>) for the information of
                        the Chinese Foreign Office.</note> was conveyed to Foreign Office. Embassy
                    has now received reply from Foreign Office dated Feb 7 stating <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Chinese Govt now expresses its willingness to cooperate with the
                            various nations in the direction of enhancing the activities of the <pb facs="0148" n="136" xml:id="pg_136"/> Far Eastern Commission and is
                            prepared to hold common discussion with the Allies in regard to any
                            relevant steps proposed to be taken.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> as 252, Feb 9, 9 a.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
